    <list list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" id="list-00015">
    <item>Is there a winner based on the first round? Why or why not?</item>
    <item>If there is a winner, who won? If there should be a runoff, who will advance to the second round?</item>
    </list>
    </problem>
    <solution id="sol-00003">
    <list list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic" id="list-00031">
    <item>A majority of 48 total votes is required to win. Begin by finding 50 percent of 48, which is calculated as follows: <math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="inline"><mrow><mn>0.50</mn><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>48</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>24</mn></mrow></math>. A majority is 25 or more. No candidate has a majority, so there is no winner based on the first round.</item>
    <item xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml">Abou and Dali advance to the second round.</item>
    </list>
    </solution>
