    <entry>Dough Boys Pizza</entry>
    <entry>2</entry>
    <entry>1</entry>
    <entry>1</entry>
    <entry>2</entry>
    <entry>1</entry>
    </row>
    </tbody>
    </tgroup>
    </table>
    <newline/><emphasis effect="bold">Step 6:</emphasis> Repeat the process from Step 2 one last time. Count the number of first place votes for each remaining restaurant.
    <para id="para-00048">Results of Round 3:</para>
    <list bullet-style="bulleted" id="list-00006">
    <item>Rainbow China — 2 votes</item>
    <item>Dough Boys — 3 votes</item></list>
    <newline/>Determine whether any one choice has a majority. Yes! Dough Boys has three votes, so it is the winner!
    </item></list>
    </solution>
    </exercise>
