    <section id="sect-00007">
    <title>Borda Count Voting</title>
    <para id="para-00081">Ranked-choice voting is one type of ranked voting that simulates multiple runoffs based on ranked ballots. Another type of ranked voting is the <emphasis effect="bold">Borda count method</emphasis>, which uses ranked ballots that award candidates points corresponding to the number of candidates ranked lower on each ballot.</para>
    <para id="para-00083">To understand how this works, let’s review the favorite colors of our kindergarten class from the table below. Let’s focus on the votes represented by the first column of the preference summary.</para>
    <table summary="." class="unnumbered" id="table-00015">
