    </example>
    <para id="para-00136"><link target-id="exam-00010" document="m00025" xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml">Example 11.10</link> illustrates the answer to the first key question. The pairwise comparison method does not always result in a winner. For example, much like the game of Rock, Paper, Scissors, it is possible for a cyclic pattern to emerge in which each candidate beats the next until the last candidate who beats the first.</para>
    <figure id="fig-00026">
    <media alt="A pie chart is split into three sections labeled Rock, Paper, and Scissors.">
